[SN]TITLE[SN]
Woman killed in car and van crash on A977 is named

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 55-year-old woman who died following a crash between a car and a van on the A977 in Perthshire on Friday morning has been named.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Brenda Donaldson, from Crook of Devon, was driving a Citroen Xsara which was involved in a collision with a Ford Transit flatbed at about 07:10.
The Kinross to Crook of Devon road was closed in both directions.
The male driver and passenger from the Ford van were treated for minor injuries at the scene.
